This message is to remind you that If you leave home, know your W’s. They are: Wear a cloth face covering, Wash your hands often or use hand sanitizer and Wait at least 6 feet away from others. These prevention practices are key to protecting our loved ones and slowing the spread of COVID-19 in our county.

Finally, if you haven’t completed your 2020 Census, we need your help. You can complete your census at my2020census.gov or by phone at 1-844-330-2020.

Please be safe and have an awesome Labor Day!

post_text: Attention Warren County Schools Parents and Students. On Monday Aug. 31, 2020 the USDA Secretary of Agriculture, Sonny Perdue, has announced in a press conference the USDA will extend the summer nutrition feeding programs through December 31, 2020, allowing every child to receive meals at no cost. Warren County School's Nutrition will continue to serve the needs of Warren County from our 3 serving sites Vaughan Elementary, Northside K-8, and Warren County High School everyday from 11:00 am until 1:00 pm including weekend meals on Friday. Have a great evening.

post_text:
History Information:
As June 19, 1865, marks the end of enslavement, September 29, 1865, marks the beginning of North Carolina freedmen collectively asserting their rights. The 1865 North Carolina Freedmen’s Convention is one of the first such conventions in the South. Held over the course of several days, the courage of these freedmen is remarkable in assembling just blocks from the state capitol and then presenting their resolution to the 1865 Constitutional Convention. A journalist who covered the Freedmen’s Convention, Sidney Andrews, describes this resolution as “one of the most remarkable documents that the time has brought forth.” Andrew further states: “This was their first political act; and I do not see how they could have presented their claims with more dignity, with a more just appreciation of the state of affairs, or in a manner which should appeal more forcibly either to the reason or the sentiment of those whom they address.”

post_text:
Important Information Concerning Warren County Schools Graduation:

1. According to the Governor, moving to phase 2 still does not allow for traditional graduation ceremonies. His offices advised schools to move forward with the May 1 guidelines which we are in compliance with. For the drive thru graduation the student may have whomever they wish to be with them in the vehicle. Students must be seated in the passenger front seat dressed in their cap and gown.

2. We have two rain dates. They are Sunday, May 31st and Saturday, June 6th both at 10 am. There will be a live stream and it will be recorded for full presentation 3 days after graduation. The live stream will be on the district's you tube page as well as the Facebook page. The sheriff's office discourages individuals from parking along hwy 158.

post_text:
Warren County Schools is now accepting applications for Pre-K and Kindergarten for the 2020- 2021 school year. To register, parents may pick up an application packet from the school in the attendance zone of their residence. Applications will be accepted April 28th through May 12th from 8:00 a.m. - 3:30 p.m. Completed applications can be returned to the school or the Central Office. To be considered for 2020-2021 Warren County Pre-K programs, a child must be 4 years old on or before August 31, 2020.
For Kindergarten, a child must be 5 years old on or before August 31, 2020. If you have additional questions please contact Ms. Monica Click at 252-257-3184.

post_text:
Parents,

Starting tomorrow, we will continue to distribute food at Vaughan ES, Northside K-8 and Warren County High School. There will be a one-time pick up of food from 11am – 4pm. This one time pick up will include a combination of breakfast and lunch/dinner items.

We understand that many of our parents don’t have transportation. As we look to assist you in providing food to our communities, we are asking that you contact us at (252) 257-3184 or complete the Google form on our website TODAY by 5pm, so we can determine the needs of our community. Once we identify the needs of our community, we will determine next steps.

Thanks again for your support and patience!

Dr. Mary Young
text:
Parents,

Starting tomorrow, we will continue to distribute food at Vaughan ES, Northside K-8 and Warren County High School. There will be a one-time pick up of food from 11am – 4pm. This one time pick up will include a combination of breakfast and lunch/dinner items.

We understand that many of our parents don’t have transportation. As we look to assist you in providing food to our communities, we are asking that you contact us at (252) 257-3184 or complete the Google form on our website TODAY by 5pm, so we can determine the needs of our community. Once we identify the needs of our community, we will determine next steps.

Thanks again for your support and patience!

Dr. Mary Young

post_text: This is a reminder to parents of 8th grade students. There will be a 9th Grade High School Registration Meeting for parents on Tuesday, March 3rd 2020 The meeting will be held at Warren County Middle School at 6:30 pm in the Multipurpose Room. The purpose of this meeting is to provide information on each of the Warren County’s High Schools and explain the process of selecting the high school that their students would like to attend as 9th graders. Warren County School’s Central Office Staff, High School Principals and Counselors will be present to provide information and answer questions. This meeting is designed to help parents and students obtain as much information as possible and fully understand their options before making their high school selection. If you have questions or need additional information, please feel free to call Ernie Conner at the Warren County Schools Central Office at 252-257-3184.

post_text: Google Certified Trainer, Carolyn Buffaloe completed the first round of training with the Warren County Schools Finance Department on using Google Applications. More training sessions will be scheduled. Good job Finance Department!

Warren County Schools has a monthly radio spotlight!!!!

Starting tomorrow, January 16th and every 3rd Thursday of the month from 11:45am-12pm, Dr. Mary L. Young will be providing monthly school district updates to our community on WARR1520. Tune in by radio or internet warr1520.
